微软研究院博客 - 微软研究院 https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/ 2024 年 6 月 5 日，星期三 16:08:16 +0000 en-US每小时1 https://wordpress.org/?v=6.5.3
微软研究院论坛第 3 集：全球包容且公平的人工智能、人工智能的新用例等https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-research-forum-episode-3-globally-inclusive-and-equitable-ai-new-use-cases-for-ai-and-更多的/Alyssa Hughes Wed, 05 Jun 2024 16:08:14 +0000Research Blog https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/?p=1043418 <p> “我们正处于生成式人工智能及其对工作影响的早期阶段。这是一个快速发展的领域，有巨大的机会来控制议程并构建真正全球公平的人工智能系统”，-Jacki O&#39;Neill，内罗毕微软非洲研究院实验室主任</p><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-research-forum-episode-3-globally-inclusive-and-equitable-ai-new-use-cases-for-ai-and-more/">微软研究院论坛第 3 集：全球包容性和公平的人工智能、人工智能的新用例等内容</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research">微软研究院</a>。</p> ; 
<p>在最新一期的<a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://researchforum.microsoft.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">微软研究论坛</a>中，研究人员探讨了全球包容性和公平人工智能的重要性，分享了<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/autogen-enabling-next-generation-large-language-model-applications/">AutoGen</a>和<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/mattergen-property-guided-materials-design/">MatterGen</a>的最新动态，介绍了人工智能的新用例，包括工业应用和多模式模型改善辅助技术的潜力。</p><p>以下是该活动的简要回顾，包括演讲中的精选引述。每个会议和演示的完整重播将很快提供。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="keynote-building-globally-equitable-ai"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/keynote-building-globally-equitable-ai/">主题演讲：构建全球公平的人工智能</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/keynote-building-globally-equitable-ai/"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="4096" height="2160" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001.png" alt="Jacki O’Neill，微软非洲研究院实验室主任，内罗毕，微软研究院论坛第 3 集" class="wp-image-1043553" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001.png 4096w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001-300x158.png 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001-1024x540.png 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001-768x405.png 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001-1536x810.png 1536w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001-2048x1080.png 2048w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/A002C006_240502XP_CANON.MXF_.10_37_22_28.Still001-240x127.png 240w" sizes="(max-width: 4096px) 100vw, 4096px" /></a></figure><p> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jaoneil/"><em>Jacki O&#39;Neill</em></a> <em>，微软非洲研究院实验室主任，内罗毕</em></p><p>Jacki O&#39;Neill 讨论了创建全球公平的生成式人工智能的重要性。她谈到了为积极改变全球工作的未来而必须解决的技术和社会技术挑战。</p><p> “我们正处于生成式人工智能及其对工作影响的早期阶段。这是一个快速发展的领域，有巨大的机会来控制议程并建立真正的全球公平的人工智能系统。这需要确保不同的环境和应用程序及其不同的数据集能够推动生成式人工智能的发展。” </p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="panel-discussion-generative-ai-for-global-impact-challenges-and-opportunities"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/panel-discussion-generative-ai-for-global-impact-challenges-and-opportunities/">小组讨论：具有全球影响力的生成式人工智能：挑战与机遇</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/panel-discussion-generative-ai-for-global-impact-challenges-and-opportunities/"><img decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001.png" alt="Jacki O’Neill，微软非洲研究院实验室主任，内罗毕（主持人） Sunayana Sitaram，微软印度研究院首席研究员 Daniela Massiceti，微软研究院高级研究员剑桥 Tanuja Ganu，微软印度研究院首席研究 SDE 经理" class="wp-image-1043556" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001.png 1920w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-300x169.png 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-1024x576.png 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-768x432.png 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-1536x864.png 1536w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-1066x600.png 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-655x368.png 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-240x135.png 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-640x360.png 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-960x540.png 960w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3B-PanelDiscussion-NEST.00_31_18_13.Still001-1280x720.png 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></a></figure><p> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jaoneil/"><em>Jacki O&#39;Neill</em></a> <em>，微软非洲研究院实验室主任，内罗毕（主持人）</em><br> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/susitara/"><em>Sunayana Sitaram</em></a> <em>，微软印度研究院首席研究员</em><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/dmassiceti/"><em>Daniela Massiceti</em></a> <em>，微软剑桥研究院高级研究员</em><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/taganu/"><em>Tanuja Ganu</em></a> <em>，微软印度研究院首席研究 SDE 经理</em></p><p>微软研究人员讨论了让人工智能对每个人更具包容性和影响力的挑战和机遇——从代表更广泛社区和文化的数据到与全球相关的人工智能新用例。</p><p> “我们如何利用生成式人工智能的力量，为全球每个人、每个人——来自不同国家、不同种族、文化以及拥有不同技术和经济承受能力的人赋权？”</p><p> <em>—Tanuja Ganu，微软印度研究院首席研究 SDE 经理</em></p><p>“我们一直在使用的解决方案之一是在实际设计时考虑到‘人参与循环’，因为我们知道这些技术并不完美。因此，我们真的想找出人类和人工智能系统可以协同工作的方法，以创造最有效的结果。”</p><p> <em>—Sunayana Sitaram，微软印度研究院首席研究员</em></p><p>“我们确实需要超越我们以前做过的任何事情的多学科研究，让研究人员、从业者和社区成员参与进来。重要的是要记住，机器学习工程师和研究人员本身无法解决构建全球公平的生成式人工智能的问题。这是我们真正需要大规模做的事情。”</p><p> <em>—Jacki O&#39;Neill，微软非洲研究院实验室主任，内罗毕</em></p><p>“目前估计有 13 亿人（约占全球人口的 16%）患有某种程度的残疾。因此，我认为看到这些生成式人工智能应用程序为这些社区上线真是令人兴奋。”</p><p> “当我们展望下一个十年的生成式人工智能解决方案时，我真的希望看到我们将看到更加个性化的人工智能模型和解决方案更加强大，在这些解决方案中，作为用户，您可以拥有更多的控制权，代理，围绕你的模型如何为你工作。”</p><p> <em>—Daniela Massiceti，微软剑桥研究院高级研究员</em></p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="lightning-talk-insights-into-the-challenges-and-opportunities-of-large-multi-modal-models-for-blind-and-low-vision-users-a-case-study-on-clip"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/insights-into-the-challenges-and-opportunities-of-large-multi-modal-models-for-blind-and-low-vision-users-a-case-study-on-clip/">闪电演讲：洞察盲人和低视力用户大型多模态模型的挑战和机遇：CLIP 案例研究</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/insights-into-the-challenges-and-opportunities-of-large-multi-modal-models-for-blind-and-low-vision-users-a-case-study-on-clip/"><img decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003.png" alt="Daniela Massiceti，微软剑桥研究院高级研究员，研究论坛第 3 集" class="wp-image-1043505" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003.png 1920w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-300x169.png 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-1024x576.png 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-768x432.png 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-1536x864.png 1536w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-1066x600.png 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-655x368.png 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-240x135.png 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-640x360.png 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-960x540.png 960w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3C-DanielaLightningTalk.00_08_48_13.Still003-1280x720.png 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></a></figure><p> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/dmassiceti/"><em>Daniela Massiceti</em></a> <em>，微软剑桥研究院高级研究员</em></p><p>Daniela Massiceti 探索了多模式模型（例如 CLIP）对于辅助技术的变革潜力。该演讲特别关注盲人/低视力群体，探讨了目前实现这一潜力的距离以及弥合这一差距所需的进步。</p><p> “当今的人工智能模型在帮助盲人社区方面具有令人难以置信的潜力——从文本识别到物体识别再到问题回答。 <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/garage/wall-of-fame/seeing-ai/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Seeing AI</a>等应用程序已经部署了其中一些 AI 功能。但还有更多的潜力。” </p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="lightning-talk-driving-industry-evolution-exploring-the-impact-of-generative-ai-on-sector-transformation"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/driving-industry-evolution-exploring-the-impact-of-generative-ai-on-sector-transformation/">闪电演讲：推动行业发展：探索生成式人工智能对行业转型的影响</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/driving-industry-evolution-exploring-the-impact-of-generative-ai-on-sector-transformation/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002.png" alt="微软亚洲研究院高级首席研究经理卞江在研究论坛第3集" class="wp-image-1043511" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002.png 1920w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-300x169.png 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-1024x576.png 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-768x432.png 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-1536x864.png 1536w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-1066x600.png 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-655x368.png 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-240x135.png 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-640x360.png 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-960x540.png 960w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3D-JiangLightningTalk.00_00_00_03.Still002-1280x720.png 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></a></figure><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jiabia/"><em>卞江</em></a><em>，微软亚洲研究院高级首席研究经理</em></p><p>边江讨论了生成式人工智能如何通过弥合人工智能能力和工业需求之间的差距来改变工业。</p><p> “在与战略合作伙伴的对话中，我们发现当前的生成式人工智能能力与行业应用的具体需求之间存在重大差距。其中包括过于狭隘地关注类人人工智能而不是关键的行业应用、处理复杂和嘈杂数据的局限性，以及对复杂决策场景可靠性的担忧。我们的研究对于解决这些局限性并放大生成式人工智能在高价值领域未被充分认识的潜力至关重要。” </p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="lightning-talk-mattergen-a-generative-model-for-materials-design"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/mattergen-a-generative-model-for-materials-design/">闪电演讲：MatterGen：材料设计的生成模型</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/mattergen-a-generative-model-for-materials-design/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001.png" alt="谢天，微软研究院首席研究经理，研究论坛第 3 集" class="wp-image-1043514" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001.png 1920w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-300x169.png 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1024x576.png 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-768x432.png 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1536x864.png 1536w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1066x600.png 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-655x368.png 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-240x135.png 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-640x360.png 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-960x540.png 960w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3E-TianLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1280x720.png 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></a></figure><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/tianxie/"><em>谢田</em></a><em>，微软研究院首席研究经理</em></p><p>谢天介绍了MatterGen，这是一种生成模型，可以根据应用所需的广泛属性条件设计新型无机材料，旨在通过生成人工智能改变材料设计的传统范式。</p><p> “传统上，材料设计是通过基于搜索的方法进行的。我们搜索候选列表，并使用应用程序的设计标准列表逐步过滤它们。与电池一样，我们需要材料含有锂、稳定、具有高锂离子电导率，并且每个过滤步骤都可以使用基于模拟的方法或人工智能模拟器进行。最后，我们得到 5 到 10 个候选者，并将其发送到实验室进行实验合成。”</p><p> “在 MatterGen，我们希望用生成式人工智能重新思考这个过程。我们的目标是根据目标应用程序的设计要求直接生成材料，绕过搜索候选的过程。你可以将其视为使用 DALL-E 等文本到图像生成模型来根据提示生成图像，而不需要通过搜索引擎在整个互联网中搜索图像。”</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="lightning-talk-autogen-update-complex-tasks-and-agents"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/autogen-update-complex-tasks-and-agents/">闪电演讲：AutoGen 更新：复杂任务和代理</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jun-2024-brief/articles/autogen-update-complex-tasks-and-agents/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001.png" alt="Adam Fourney，微软人工智能前沿研究院首席研究员，在研究论坛第 3 集" class="wp-image-1043535" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001.png 1920w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-300x169.png 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1024x576.png 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-768x432.png 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1536x864.png 1536w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1066x600.png 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-655x368.png 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-240x135.png 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-640x360.png 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-960x540.png 960w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/06/E3F-AdamLightningTalk.00_00_00_00.Still001-1280x720.png 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /></a></figure><p> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/adamfo/"><em>Adam Fourney</em></a> <em>，微软人工智能前沿研究院首席研究员</em></p><p>Adam Fourney 讨论了使用多个代理协同工作来完成复杂的多步骤任务的有效性。他展示了他们在 GAIA 等基准上超越以前单代理解决方案的能力，利用可定制的代理安排，这些代理进行协作、推理和利用工具来实现复杂的结果。</p><p> “我们开始使用这种配置来应对日益复杂的基准测试和现实场景。我们对引入新代理的机会感到非常兴奋，例如，通过经验学习和自我改进；更好地理解图像和屏幕截图，以便更有效地上网或使用界面；这对于探索解决方案空间可能更加系统化。因此，他们不只是更新账本，然后在遇到困难时重新启动，他们可以对所采用的策略更加务实一些。”</p><span id="label-external-link" class="sr-only" aria-hidden="true">在新选项卡中打开</span><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-research-forum-episode-3-globally-inclusive-and-equitable-ai-new-use-cases-for-ai-and-more/">微软研究院论坛第 3 集：全球包容性和公平的人工智能、人工智能的新用例等内容</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research">微软研究院</a>。</p> ;
微软在 FAccT 2024：推进负责任的人工智能研究和实践https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-at-facct-2024-advancing-responsible-ai-research-and-practice/Brenda Potts Wed, 05 Jun 2024 16:00:00 +0000Research Blog https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/?p=1041459 <p>从研究如何识别印地语中的性别偏见到发现员工与人工智能相关的风险，微软正在为推进负责任的人工智能研究的最新技术做出重要贡献。查看他们在 ACM FaccT 2024 上的工作。</p><p> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-at-facct-2024-advancing-responsible-ai-research-and-practice/">微软在 FAccT 2024 上的帖子：推进负责任的人工智能研究和实践</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research">微软研究院</a>。</p> ; 
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="微软参加 ACM FACCT 2024" class="wp-image-1041477" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-960x540.jpg 960w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1-1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prodnew/2024/05/FAccT-Curation-2024-BlogHeroFeature-1400x788-1.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure><p>人工智能和其他计算技术的集成在金融、医疗保健和政府等高风险领域变得越来越普遍，它们影响关键决策的能力正在不断增强。虽然这些系统提供了许多好处，但它们也带来了风险，例如根深蒂固的系统性偏见和减少问责制。 <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/event/facct-2024/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">ACM 公平、问责和透明度会议</a>(ACM FaccT 2024) 旨在解决这些问题，汇集了来自各个学科、致力于负责任地开发计算系统的专家。</p><p> Microsoft 很荣幸再次成为 ACM FAccT 2024 的赞助商，这突显了我们对支持负责任的人工智能研究的承诺。我们很高兴地告诉大家，我们团队的成员在组织活动、为项目委员会做出贡献以及担任项目联合主席方面发挥了关键作用。此外，微软研究人员及其合作者的七篇论文已被该计划接受，其中“Akal badi yabias：印地语语言技术中性别偏见的探索性研究”获得了最佳论文奖。</p><p>总的来说，这些研究项目强调需要反映<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/ai/principles-and-approach" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Microsoft Responsible AI</a>原则的 AI 技术，这些原则包括问责制、包容性、可靠性和安全性、公平性、透明度以及隐私和安全性。他们强调解决与部署和使用相关的潜在风险和危害的重要性。这篇文章重点介绍了这些进展。 </p><div class="border-bottom border-top border-gray-300 mt-5 mb-5 msr-promo text-center text-md-left alignwide" data-bi-aN="promo" data-bi-id="670821"><p class="msr-promo__label text-gray-800 text-center text-uppercase"><span class="px-4 bg-white display-inline-block font-weight-semibold small">焦点：微软研究通讯</span></p><div class="row pt-3 pb-4 align-items-center"><div class="msr-promo__media col-12 col-md-5"> <a class="bg-gray-300" href="https://info.microsoft.com/ww-landing-microsoft-research-newsletter.html" aria-label="Microsoft Research Newsletter" data-bi-cN="Microsoft Research Newsletter" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" class="w-100 display-block" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2019/09/Newsletter_Banner_08_2019_v1_1920x1080.png" alt="" /></a></div><div class="msr-promo__content p-3 px-5 col-12 col-md"><h2 class="h4">微软研究院通讯</h2><p class="large">与 Microsoft 研究社区保持联系。 </p><div class="wp-block-buttons justify-content-center justify-content-md-start"><div class="wp-block-button is-style-fill-chevron"> <a href="https://info.microsoft.com/ww-landing-microsoft-research-newsletter.html" class="btn btn-brand glyph-append glyph-append-chevron-right" aria-label="Microsoft Research Newsletter" data-bi-cN="Microsoft Research Newsletter" target="_blank">立即订阅</a></div></div></div><!--/.msr-promo__content--></div><!--/.msr-promo__inner-wrap--><span id="label-external-link" class="sr-only" aria-hidden="true">在新选项卡中打开</span></div><!--/.msr-promo--><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="paper-highlights">论文亮点</h2><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/a-framework-for-exploring-the-consequences-of-ai-mediated-enterprise-knowledge-access-and-identifying-risks-to-workers/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">用于探索人工智能介导的企业知识获取的后果并识别工人风险的框架</a></h3><p><em>安娜·高森，</em><strong><em> </em></strong><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/bmitra/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>巴斯卡·</em></a><em>米特拉</em><strong><em> </em></strong><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/sianl/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>西安·林德利</em></a></p><p>最近的人工智能发展，尤其是法学硕士，正在显着影响组织知识的获取和重塑工作场所。这些人工智能系统由于与组织权力动态的相互作用而带来风险。本文介绍了后果-机制-风险框架，以帮助识别工人风险，并将其分类为与价值、权力和福祉相关的问题。该框架旨在帮助从业者减轻这些风险并将其应用于其他技术，从而更好地保护工人。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/a-structured-regression-approach-for-evaluating-model-performance-across-intersectional-subgroups/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">用于评估跨交叉子组的模型性能的结构化回归方法</a></h3><p><em>Christine Herlihy、Kimberly Truong、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/alexandrac/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Alex Chouldechova</em></a> <em>、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/mdudik/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Miro Dudík</em></a></p><p>分类评估是人工智能公平性评估中使用的一个过程，用于衡量不同子组的人工智能系统性能。这些子组是由人口统计或其他敏感属性混合定义的。然而，交叉亚组的样本量通常非常小，导致它们被排除在分析之外。这项工作引入了一种结构化回归方法，可以在这些子组中进行更可靠的系统性能估计。该方法在两个公开可用的数据集和半合成数据的几种变体上进行了测试，不仅产生了更准确的结果，而且还有助于识别导致性能差异的关键因素。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/akal-badi-ya-bias-an-exploratory-study-of-gender-bias-in-hindi-language-technology/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Akal badi ya 偏见：印地语语言技术中性别偏见的探索性研究</a></h3><p><em>最佳论文奖</em></p><p><em>Rishav Hada、Safiya Husain、Varun Gumma、Harshita Diddee、Aditya Yadavalli、</em> <a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.si.umich.edu/people/agrima-seth" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Agrima Seth</em></a> <em>、Nidhi Kulkarni、Ujwal Gadiraju、</em> <a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.adityavashistha.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Aditya Vashistha</em></a> <em>、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/visesha/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Vivek Seshadri</em></a> <em>、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/kalikab/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Kalika Bali</em></a></p><p>现有关于语言技术中性别偏见的研究主要集中在英语上，往往忽视非英语语言。本文介绍了第一个关于印地语性别偏见的综合研究，印地语是全球第三大语言。作者采用多种技术和实地研究，揭示了当前方法的局限性，并强调需要进行更多针对具体情况和以社区为中心的研究。这些发现加深了对印地语语言技术中性别偏见的理解，并为扩大对其他印度语言的研究奠定了基础。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/im-not-sure-but-examining-the-impact-of-large-language-models-uncertainty-expression-on-user-reliance-and-trust/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">“我不确定，但是……”：检查大型语言模型的不确定性表达对用户依赖和信任的影响</a></h3><p><em>Sunnie SY Kim、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/veraliao/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Q. Vera Liao</em></a> <em>、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/mivorvor/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Mihaela Vorvoreanu</em></a> <em>、Stephanie Ballard、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jenn/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>Jennifer Wortman Vaughan</em></a></p><p>法学硕士可以产生令人信服但不正确的答案，可能会误导依赖其准确性的用户。为了缓解这个问题，有人建议法学硕士在其回答中传达不确定性。在一项关于用户如何看待法学硕士表达不确定性并采取行动的大规模研究中，参与者被问及医学问题。作者发现，第一人称不确定性表达（例如，“我不确定，但是……”）降低了参与者对系统的信心以及他们同意系统答案的倾向，同时提高了他们自己答案的准确性。相比之下，更一般的不确定性表达（例如，“不清楚，但是……”）的效果较差。研究结果强调了在部署法学硕士之前进行更彻底的用户测试的重要性。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/investigating-and-designing-for-trust-in-ai-powered-code-generation-tools/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">调查和设计人工智能驱动的代码生成工具的信任</a></h3><p><em>王若彤、程瑞嘉、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/denae/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>德娜·福特</em></a><em>、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/tzimmer/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>汤姆·齐默尔曼</em></a></p><p>随着 GitHub Copilot 等工具越来越受欢迎，了解软件开发人员对这些应用程序的信任对于它们的采用和负责任的使用变得至关重要。在一项两阶段的定性研究中，作者采访了 17 名开发人员，以了解他们在建立对 AI 代码生成工具的信任时面临的挑战。确定的挑战包括设定期望、配置工具和验证建议。作者还探索了几种设计概念，以帮助开发人员建立适当的信任，并为人工智能驱动的代码生成工具提供设计建议。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/less-discriminatory-algorithms/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">较少歧视的算法</a></h3><p><em>艾米丽·布莱克、洛根·科普克、宝琳·金、<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/solon/">索伦·巴罗卡斯</a>、徐明伟</em></p><p>在住房、就业和信贷等领域，使用算法系统的组织应寻求使用歧视性较小的替代方案。计算机科学研究表明，对于任何预测问题，多种算法都可以提供相同水平的准确性，但对不同人口群体的影响不同。这种现象被称为模型多重性，表明开发人员也许能够找到性能相同但可能较少歧视的替代方案。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading h5" id="title"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/participation-in-the-age-of-foundation-models/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">参与基础模型时代</a></h3><p><em>哈里尼·苏雷什、曾艾米丽、梅格·杨、</em> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/mlg/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>玛丽·格雷</em></a><em>、艾玛·皮尔森、凯伦·利维</em></p><p>公共服务中基金会模式的兴起既带来了潜在的好处，也带来了风险，包括加剧权力失衡和伤害边缘群体。本文探讨了如何将参与式人工智能/机器学习方法（通常是特定于上下文的）适应这些与上下文无关的模型，从而为受影响最严重的人提供帮助。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="conference-organizers-from-microsoft">微软的会议组织者</h2><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="program-co-chair">项目联合主席</h3><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/aloltea/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">亚历山德拉·奥尔泰亚努</a></p><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="program-committee">程序委员会</h3><p><a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ballardstephanie/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">斯蒂芬·巴拉德</a><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/solon/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">索伦·巴罗卡斯</a><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/sublodge/">苏林·布洛吉特</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/kate/">凯特·克劳福德</a><br><a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/shipidhanorkar/">什皮·达诺卡</a><br><a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/amy-heger/">艾米·黑格</a><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jmh/">杰克·霍夫曼</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/emrek/">埃姆雷·基西曼</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/veraliao/">廖薇拉</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/dmassiceti/">丹妮拉·马塞蒂</a><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/bmitra/">巴斯卡·米特拉</a><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/benushi/">贝斯米拉·努什</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/aloltea/">亚历山德拉·奥尔泰亚努</a><br><a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/amifaraj/">阿米法·拉吉</a><br><a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/emily-s-21b95b6a/">盛艾米丽</a><br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jenn/">詹妮弗·沃特曼·沃恩</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/mivorvor/">米哈埃拉·沃尔沃雷亚努</a>*<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/dwilkinson/">达里西亚·威尔金森</a><br><br>*区域主席</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-opportunities">工作机会</h2><p>Microsoft 欢迎 Microsoft Research、Azure Research 和其他部门的各种职位的优秀人才。我们始终致力于突破计算机系统的界限，以提高我们所有产品的规模、效率和安全性。您可以<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/careers/">在此处</a>查看我们与研究相关的开放职位。</p><div style="height:30px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div><span id="label-external-link" class="sr-only" aria-hidden="true">在新选项卡中打开</span><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-at-facct-2024-advancing-responsible-ai-research-and-practice/">微软在 FAccT 2024 上的帖子：推进负责任的人工智能研究和实践</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research">微软研究院</a>。</p> ;
